			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Sr. Sales Executive, Mid Markets</strong></p>
<p>
<strong>Position Summary</strong><br />
The Mid Markets group sells to companies from $0 to $500 Mill. in revenue.&nbsp; Sell to the Line of Business professional (Training, Mkting, Sales, Channels) within those companies to help generate mind share, drive revenue, reduce costs and communicate utilizing the Brainshark product suite.&nbsp; This role is 100% new business acquisition from new customers.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities</strong><br />
&bull; Consistently meet or exceed assigned revenue quota associated with management and development of new customer sales opportunities within assigned territory.<br />
&bull; Design and implement a sales strategy &amp; territory plan including but, not limited to the following: a targeted accounts list, strategic email campaigns, customized presentations/demonstrations via web and live.<br />
&bull; Proactively follow-up on all opportunities generated by marketing campaigns.<br />
&bull; Employ a proven sales process to take prospects from initial interest, build business value, develop proof of concept, deliver custom proposal, and contract closure.<br />
&bull; Develop relationships with industry groups, and potential referral agents who can make connections to desired prospects.<br />
&bull; Provide &amp; maintain an accurate 3-4 month rolling forecast and track sales activity in Salesforce.com.<br />
&bull; Consistently meet or exceed assigned quota of sales metrics tracked in Salesforce.com.<br />
Requirements<br />
&bull; BS, BA degree or equivalent<br />
&bull; 5+ years of experience selling software product/solutions in B2B environment<br />
&bull; Proven track record of selling and presenting in person, on the phone, and via web conference to senior executives<br />
&bull; Experience developing relationships with customer&#39;s senior management by speaking in terms of business value<br />
&bull; Strong written and verbal communication skills<br />
&bull; Ability and willingness for 10% travel in U.S. and Canada (location depends on territory assigned)</p>
<p>
<strong>Desired Knowledge/Skills</strong><br />
&bull; A history of sales results above quota, and in the top 10% of peers<br />
&bull; Sales experience of business user applications is preferred over back office IT department applications<br />
&bull; Sales experience of SaaS applications is preferred over premise-based, installed software<br />
&bull; Sales experience with an application that requires a customer&rsquo;s change in process is preferred over a vendor replacement sale (doing the same thing, just with a new vendor)<br />
&bull; Experience building a solution involving multiple users and departments is preferred over sales to a single user/department<br />
&bull; Experience hunting for new customers is preferred over experience renewing/growing existing accounts<br />
&bull; Direct sales experience is preferred over channel sales<br />
&bull; Ability to conceptualize business ideas with visuals including a good understanding of MS Powerpoint<br />
Reports to Director of Sales.&nbsp; Sales execs work out of HQ office in Waltham unless traveling to customers. Will not pay for relocation. Position is open for immediate hire. Send resumes to jobs@brainshark.com or reply directly to this ad.</p>
<p>
<strong>Company Description</strong></p>
<p>
Brainshark provides the leading cloud-based platform for sales enablement, helping companies more effectively prepare and train employees, engage with key audiences and advance business opportunities. Brainshark&#39;s easy-to-use solutions enable static documents to be transformed into dynamic, mobile-ready content that can be accessed quickly and viewed as on-demand video presentations or presented live&mdash;anytime, anywhere. Customers can also measure the effectiveness of their communications in ways never thought possible and use these insights to take action. Thousands of companies&mdash;including half of the Fortune 100 and millions of individuals&mdash;rely on Brainshark to increase the impact and reduce the cost of their sales, marketing, training and HR communications. For more information, visit <a href="http://www.brainshark.com">www.brainshark.com</a>.</p>
<p>
<br />
If you&#39;re a talented, creative and high-energy person, we want you on the Brainshark team! Why work here? Brainshark is a fun, dynamic, fast-growing company. We have a team of smart, motivated contributors who love to roll up their sleeves. If you&#39;d like to help build innovative technology and a great company, we&#39;d like to hear from you.<br />
Brainshark offers a competitive compensation and benefit package including:<br />
&bull; Medical<br />
&bull; Dental<br />
&bull; 401K<br />
&bull; Flexible spending plans<br />
&bull; Disability<br />
&bull; Life insurance<br />
&bull; On site fitness center<br />
&bull; Generous vacation time</p>
<p>
<br />
Brainshark is an Equal Opportunity Employer. We welcome and encourage diversity in the workplace.</p>
